The paper deals with the problem of self-localization in a network using radio signal strength indicator (RSSI) measurements and anchor node position information subject to perturbations. This problem is relevant to the field of networked systems and wireless sensor networks, which fall under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of statistical methods such as normal and log-normal distributions, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The optimization algorithm used in the paper is based on gradient descent, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the development of an algorithm for self-localization, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
